Colombian Stocks: Almacenes Exito Falls; Avianca Taca Rises

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-08-31T16:33:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/colombian-stocks-almacenes-exito-falls-avianca-taca-rises.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:16 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.1 percent to 13,487.55, while the
Colcap Index fell 0.1 percent to 1,639.03.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  fell after  Colombia ’s biggest publicly
traded retailer said it will offer shares in the local market at
a 9.6 percent discount from yesterday’s closing price.  The stock declined 2.2 percent to 23,300 pesos, after
earlier falling as much as 5.5 percent, the most in two months.  Avianca Taca Holding SA (PFAVTA CB), owner of Colombia’s
largest airline, rose 0.7 percent to 4,605 pesos. The company
said the number of passengers rose 17 percent from a year ago to
a record 1.9 million in July, according to an e-mailed statement
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
